# ===========================================
# ArchAI Planner - API Configuration
# ===========================================

# OpenAI API Configuration
# Get your key from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
OPENAI_API_KEY=your-openai-api-key-here

# Supabase Database Configuration
# Get these from: https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/_/settings/api
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-supabase-anon-key-here

# Backend Functions Configuration (Optional)
# Use this if you deploy secure backend functions instead of direct OpenAI calls
RORK_FUNCTIONS_URL=https://your-backend-functions-url.com

# ===========================================
# Setup Instructions:
# ===========================================
# 1. Copy this file to .env:
#    cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. Replace placeholder values with your actual API keys
#
# 3. Add .env to .gitignore (already done)
#
# 4. Restart Xcode after making changes
#
# ===========================================
# Security Notes:
# ===========================================
# - NEVER commit .env file to version control
# - Use different keys for development and production
# - Rotate API keys regularly
# - Monitor API usage and costs
#
# ===========================================
# Demo Mode:
# ===========================================
# If API keys are missing or invalid, the app will:
# - Automatically fall back to demo mode
# - Show sample AI-generated projects
# - Use mock AI responses
# - Display configuration warnings
# - Still provide full UI functionality
#
# ===========================================
# Where to get API keys:
# ===========================================
#
# OpenAI API Key:
# 1. Go to https://platform.openai.com/
# 2. Sign up or log in
# 3. Navigate to API Keys section
# 4. Click "Create new secret key"
# 5. Copy the key (starts with "sk-")
# 6. Add as OPENAI_API_KEY
#
# Supabase Configuration:
# 1. Go to https://supabase.com/
# 2. Create new project or select existing
# 3. Go to Settings > API
# 4. Copy Project URL and anon public key
# 5. Add as SUPABASE_URL and SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
#
# Backend Functions (Optional):
# 1. Deploy functions to Netlify, Vercel, or similar
# 2. Get the deployed URL
# 3. Add as RORK_FUNCTIONS_URL
# 4. See SETUP_GUIDE.md for function examples
